detaileddescription.para: A place to enter values (of any data type) that are directly associated with, and attached to, a selected answer choice.

briefdescription.para: Represents the default value of the ListItem in the FormDesign template, or the user's response in selecting one or more ListItems. If ='false' on ListField then only one item may be selected.

If set to true, then selecting this ListItem must deactivate all descendant parts of the form, and ignore any user-entered values in the deactivated part. Deselecting the ListItem should reactivate the descendant items in their state at the time the items were deactivated.

detaileddescription.para: If set to true, then selecting this ListItem must deactivate all descendant parts of the form, and ignore any user-entered values in the deactivated part. Deselecting the ListItem should reactivate the descendant items in their state at the time the items were deactivated.
If items are disabled, then any data stored in the disabled questions should be removed.

briefdescription.para: NEW Selecting the current ListItem will enable the named items in this attribute's content.

detaileddescription.para: Prefixing any named with a hyphen (-) will reverse the above behaviour (i.e., the named items will be disabled).
Unselecting the ListItem will reverse this behaviour. Prefixing the name with a tilde (~) will supress this reversal behavior.

briefdescription.para: NEW Selecting the current ListItem will select the named ListItems in this attribute's content.

detaileddescription.para: Prefixing any named with a hyphen (-) will reverse the above behaviour.
Unselecting the ListItem will reverse this behaviour. Prefixing the name with a tilde (~) will supress this reversal behavior.

briefdescription.para: If the ancestor ListField has = 'true', then selecting this ListItem should de-select all other ListItem (sibling) nodes except the current one.
NEW
NEW: Selecting the current ListItem will cause the named items in the list (or any other list) to be de-selected. All named items must be prefixed with the $ symbol, and must point to ListItems.
NEW:

detaileddescription.para: If is set to true, then the question and its response(s) should not be present in a typical report derived from this template. This attribute is usually set to true when the answer choice is used to control form behavior (e.g., skip logic), or when the question provides unhelpful "negative" information about actions that did not occur or were not performed, or things that were not observed or could not be assessed. If is false (default) then the question and its response(s) should appear in the report. Added 11/29/15 to replace
